    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-style-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> diced chicken thigh</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-style-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-style-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add the<strong> sliced shallot </strong>and<strong> diced pepper </strong>with the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-style-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong>, <strong>gluten free soy sauce</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> fish sauce</strong>,<strong> </strong>1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> water</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce begins to reduce and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-style-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, crack your<strong> egg[s]</strong> into the pan and cook, covered, for 2 min or until done to your liking \u2013 this is your<strong> fried egg</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-style-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, remove the pan from the heat</p><p>Pick your<strong> Thai basil leaves</strong> from their stalks, discard the stalks</p><p>Add the<strong> Thai basil leaves</strong> to the chicken and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> fragrant Thai-style chicken stir-fry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-thai-style-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>fragrant Thai-style chicken stir-fry</strong> over the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Top with a <strong>fried egg</strong></p><p>Garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
